"meanings":["From an Old English personal name derived from <i>ælf</i> ‘elf, supernatural being’ + <i>wine</i> ‘friend’. This was not especially common in Britain either before or after the Norman Conquest, but it is popular in the United States. The reasons for this are not entirely clear; association with   Calvin   may be a factor. A more plausible (though less elevated) explanation is that this was the name given to the naughty chipmunk in a popular television cartoon series of the 1960s."],"variants":[{"name":"Aylwin","meanings":["Variant of   Alvin ."]}]},{"name":"Oge","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a Danish vernacular form of <i>Aghi</i>, a short form of the various names of Old Norse origin containing the element <i>ag</i> ‘edge (of a weapon)’ or ‘awe, terror’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Miss Alwyn Oge MacMurdac was born in 1130 as the daughter of Alanus de Leche. She married Gilchrist Bretnach from 1165 to 1170, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1190, in Stirlingshire, Scotland, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1130–1190":"1130–1190","1155–1217":"1155–1217","1160–1214":"1160–1214","1168–Male":"1168–Surnud","1175–Male":"1175–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","1140–1242":"1140–1242","1170–1242":"1170–1242","1170–Male":"1170–Surnud","1130–1199":"1130–1199","1190":"1190","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1242":"1242","1175":"1175","1130":"1130","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1170":"1170","1217":"1217","from 1165 to 1170":"1165 kuni 1170","1214":"1214","1168":"1168","1199":"1199","1155":"1155","Scotland":"Scotland","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1130–1190":"1130–1190","1155–1217":"1155–1217","1160–1214":"1160–1214","1168–Male":"1168–Kuollut","1175–Male":"1175–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","1140–1242":"1140–1242","1170–1242":"1170–1242","1170–Male":"1170–Kuollut","1130–1199":"1130–1199","1190":"1190","about 1170":"noin 117